What is Flask?
Flask is python webframework which contains set of dependencies and libraries .
FLask starts the web server which listens to port 5000.
It provides components needed to build web app such as routing, templte rendering,request andling, response generation.

Why do we use render_template()?
To render the page in UI. It reads HTML template from templates folder  and returns HTTP reponse to browser.

Why do we have a templates folder?
We can use multiple HTML pages inside a folder which can be accessed by flask app.
If we dont use templates folder, html files will be randomly spread, it wont be a good project structure.

